Idea:
Run three commands by writing 
git save 

if you want to write commit message 
git acp

Logic in git:
$ cat ~/.gitconfig
[user]
        name = MD-NABEEL-T
        email = tmdnabeel4656.tmn@gmail.com
[core]
        autocrlf = false
[alias]
        acp = !sh -c \"git add . && git commit -m \\\"$1\\\" && git push\" -
        save = !git add . && git commit -m \"auto\" && git push
